<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Movie Search Results</title>
    <!-- Link Swiper's CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/swiper@11/swiper-bundle.min.css" />
    <style>
        html,
        body {
            position: relative;
            height: 100%;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        body {
            background: #141414;
            font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #fff;
        }

        .swiper {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
        }

        .swiper-slide {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 18px;
            background-color: #333;
            height: calc((100% - 30px) / 2) !important;
            /* Center slide text vertically */
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .swiper-slide a {
            color: #fff;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .swiper-slide img {
            width: 80%; /* Decreased image size */
            height: auto;
        }

        .swiper-pagination-bullet {
            background: #e50914; /* Netflix red */
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Swiper -->
    <div class="swiper mySwiper">
        <div class="swiper-wrapper movie-cards">
            <% movies.forEach(movie => { %>
            <div class="swiper-slide box card">
                <a href="/movie/<%= movie.id %>">
                    <div class="box-img">
                        <img src="https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w200<%= movie.poster_path %>" alt="<%= movie.title %> poster">
                    </div>
                    <h3><%= movie.title %></h3>
                </a>
            </div>
            <% }) %>
        </div>
        <div class="swiper-pagination"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Swiper JS -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/swiper@11/swiper-bundle.min.js"></script>

    <!-- Initialize Swiper -->
    <script>
        var swiper = new Swiper(".mySwiper", {
            slidesPerView: 3,
            grid: {
                rows: 2,
            },
            spaceBetween: 30,
            pagination: {
                el: ".swiper-pagination",
                clickable: true,
            },
        });
    </script>
</body>

</html>
It is imperative that the capstone project employs the POST method exclusively for the sign-in and sign-up processes. This ensures secure and authenticated user interactions with the application, as POST requests are designed for data submission and are better suited for handling sensitive information.

Password Hashing in Sign-Up Functionality:
Before storing user passwords in the database during the sign-up process, it is mandatory to hash the supplied passwords. Hashing is a crucial security measure that transforms the password into an irreversible string of characters, adding an extra layer of protection to user data. (This project is covered in capstone project live class)

Email Duplication Prevention in Sign-Up Functionality:
To maintain data integrity and user uniqueness, the application must validate that the email provided during sign-up has not been used before. If an email address is already associated with an existing account, the system should detect this and return an error, ensuring that each email address is linked to only one account.